## CHUNK 1 — M2 + M3: contract extension + universal injection
*(prompt-only; shippable alone; immediately cuts novelty crash rate. CHECKPOINT after this
chunk before Chunk 2.)*

### Step 1.1 — [SCOUT] Locate the existing contract summary
Find where the current contract text lives (the evaluator brief + interface contract that
mutation prompts already inject — likely a constant/template in `py_mutation_engine.py` or a
text file the builders read). Report: its exact location, current content, and the injection
mechanism (which builders include it, via what variable/function).

### Step 1.2 — Extend the contract (agent AUDITS, human signs off)
Write the two known missing sections, then audit for more:
- **Data contract**: read the baseline candidate's code (`--baseline-py` file / try_000) and the
  evaluator; document exactly: what `context` carries (keys, types), the data file paths/format,
  feature matrix + label shape, class balance note if the contract mentions it. A generated init
  candidate must be able to load data from THIS text alone.
- **Serialization constraints**: state as hard rules: (1) any custom class MUST be module-level —
  classes defined inside functions (`<locals>`) cannot be pickled, ever; (2) prefer bare sklearn
  estimators (the evaluator's size introspection reads attributes like `tree_`/`coef_`);
  (3) save via the existing convention (joblib.dump to model.pkl) exactly as the interface
  contract states.
- **AUDIT**: compare the assembled contract against the real evaluator + runner behavior. If you
  find contract-relevant facts a from-scratch candidate would need and the text omits (e.g.
  timeout budget, expected metric names, working-directory assumptions, allowed imports),
  DRAFT each as a proposed section and STOP — present them as OPTIONS for human sign-off. Do
  NOT silently add sections.

### Step 1.3 — Inject into every operator prompt (M3)
Wire the extended contract into `build_improve_feedback`, `build_combine_feedback`,
`build_repair_feedback`, `build_novelty_feedback` — **[MATCH]** the existing injection pattern
found in 1.1 (if some builders already include the old summary, extend in place; if any builder
lacks it, add it in the same position/style as the others). One source of truth; builders
reference it, never copy it.

### Chunk 1 verification
1. Run a short search (`--tries 10`+). Open `tries/try_*/prompt.txt` for one try of EACH
   operation: the extended contract block appears, identical text, in all of them.
2. Eye test on any novelty try produced: generated code defines classes at module level (no
   `<locals>`), or uses bare estimators. If a novelty candidate still pickle-crashes with a
   `<locals>` class, the contract text is not landing or not clear — STOP and report.
3. Report the input-token delta per call (prompt.txt size before/after) so the human sees the
   cost of universal injection.

